description: Almost 4,000 tests were carried out as part of a government study to measure the spread of the virus.
title: Coronavirus: Isle of Man antibody tests show 2,500 may have had Covid-19
title_page: Coronavirus: Isle of Man antibody tests show 2,500 may have had Covid-19 - BBC News
maintext: The results so far estimate that between 1,680 and 2,520 of the island's population of 84,000 may have had Covid-19 to date - a maximum of 3%.
